# ${{ values.name }}

${{ values.description }}

A monorepo pairing a Strapi headless CMS (`apps/cms`) with a React frontend (`apps/web`), scaffolded by the platform self-service catalog.

## Layout

- `apps/cms` Strapi headless CMS, generated on first setup (see step 2).
- `apps/web` Vite, React and TypeScript frontend wired to the CMS REST API.

## 1. Start the database

```bash
cp .env.example .env
npm run db:up
```

## 2. Bootstrap the CMS

Strapi projects are generated by its own CLI. Run this once to create `apps/cms`:

```bash
npx create-strapi-app@latest apps/cms --no-run --dbclient=postgres \
  --dbname=strapi --dbusername=strapi --dbpassword=strapi --dbhost=localhost --dbport=5432
cd apps/cms && npm run develop
```

The admin panel is served at http://localhost:1337/admin.

## 3. Run the frontend

```bash
npm install
npm run web
```

The frontend reads the CMS URL from `VITE_STRAPI_URL` (defaults to http://localhost:1337).
